thread.title: Jetco Delivery promotes new president

author: Laura Furr
title: Jetco Delivery promotes new president
text:
Brian Fielkow has assumed the role of CEO of Houston-based Jetco Delivery LLC. Former… more Houston-based Jetco Delivery LLC appointed Kyle Kristynik as the company's new president. Kristynik previously served as the company's vice president of finance and administration. He joined the company in 2012 as finance and accounting manager, according to a release from the company. Current owner and president Brian Fielkow has assumed the role of CEO. "Jetco has experienced tremendous growth over the past several years, and I am ready to continue to help make Jetco the best in the business,” Kristynik said in a statement. “Our team and our culture is what makes us who we are and allows us to safely service our customers." Kristynik played a key role in the company's transition to its new 20-acre corporate headquarters on Aldine Bender Drive in north Houston, according to the statement. The new ergonomic headquarters is stocked with employee perks and features to retain and attract employees. Jetco was named one of Houston's fastest-growing private companies in 2011 . Last year, the company earned $31.5 million in revenue .
